relatedItem.abstract: From the HMT description: "Escorial Ω.I.12 (=Allen’s E4, West F) is an 11th century parchment codex, thought by Allen to be later than Υ.1.1, consisting of 216 folios containing a complete text of the Iliad, a commentary with lemmata on Iliad 1–2.300, hypotheses, lives of Homer, a summary of the Cypria and the Batrachomyomachia (“Battle of Frogs and Mice”), excerpts from Porphyry, and other scholia. "
